---
name: FastAPI Rules
globs:
  - "src/routes/**/*.py"
  - "src/api/**/*.py"
  - "main.py"
---

## Endpoints
- All endpoint functions must be async def — never plain def
- Every endpoint must have a response_model parameter defined
- All request bodies must be typed with a Pydantic model — no raw dicts
- Always raise HTTPException for errors, never generic Python exceptions
- Use APIRouter to group related endpoints — register all routers in main.py
- Add a docstring to every endpoint — FastAPI renders these in /docs

## Pydantic Models
- Define all request and response models in a dedicated schemas.py file
- Always set model config to forbid extra fields to prevent unexpected input
- Optional fields must have a default value — never leave them bare
- Use Field() to add validation constraints and description text

## Project Structure
- Routes go in src/routes/, one file per resource (weather.py, events.py)
- Business logic goes in src/services/ — never inside the route handler
- Database access goes in src/db/ — never directly inside routes
- Environment variables must be loaded via a config.py using pydantic-settings

## Response Shape
- Responses must match the endpoint contract exactly (no global envelope unless the endpoint spec requires it)
- Current required contracts:
  - GET /health -> { "status": "ok", "readings_stored": <int>, "events_stored": <int> }
  - GET /readings -> { "readings": [ ... ] }
  - GET /events -> { "events": [ ... ] }
- Never return raw SQLAlchemy model instances — always serialize through
  a Pydantic response model first
- Empty results return 200 with an empty list, not a 404